Name: env2json
Version: 2020.12.3
Summary: .env -> .env.json
Home-page: https://github.com/andrewp-as-is/env2json.py
License: Unlicense
Description: <!--
        https://readme42.com
        -->
        
        
        [![](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/env2json.svg?maxAge=3600)](https://pypi.org/project/env2json/)
        [![](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-Unlicense-blue.svg?longCache=True)](https://unlicense.org/)
        
        ### Installation
        ```bash
        $ [sudo] pip install env2json
        ```
        
        #### Examples
        `.env.dev`
        ```bash
        DB_NAME=name
        DB_USER=username
        DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
        DB_PORT=5432
        ```
        
        ```bash
        $ python -m env2json .env.dev > .env.dev.json
        ```
        
        `.env.dev.json`
        ```json
        {
          "DB_HOST": "127.0.0.1",
          "DB_NAME": "name",
          "DB_PORT": "5432",
          "DB_USER": "username"
        }
        ```
        
